<item>
            <title>[SPR-2015] action parameter for spring-form taglib should be mandatory or a reasonable default should be written to output</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2015</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The form tag of the spring-form taglib generates invalid HTML output. The action parameter &lt;em&gt;IS&lt;/em&gt; required, so spring should output a reasonable default (the same URI) or declare the action parameter mandatory. I know that it is a common practice to omit this parameter in HTML, but this is not spec conform.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="13971">SPR-2015</key>
            <summary>action parameter for spring-form taglib should be mandatory or a reasonable default should be written to output</summary>
