                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17803" author="cnelson" created="Wed, 31 May 2006 09:11:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that action=&quot;&quot; and action=&quot;#&quot; are both valid and neither should break any existing code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17804" author="ojs" created="Wed, 31 May 2006 16:42:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, but note that older browsers (Netscape 4 for e.g.) can&apos;t handle action=&quot;&quot; (I don&apos;t know if it can handle action=&quot;#&quot;). So, this drawback should get documented at least - or even better, spring should output the current url (which is, what current browsers do when action=&quot;&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18834" author="diggerdig" created="Mon, 31 Jul 2006 07:04:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a problem with the fix for this as it is currently implemented.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the form tag has no action attribute and a mapping is used to get to the action address the resolveAction() method gets the URI and emits, for example,  action=&quot;/i04marketing/WEB-INF/jsp/tiles/root.jsp?commercialId=1&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is obviously not going to work as a submit destination.&lt;br/&gt;
A few people have been having a problem with this as can be seen in this thread - &lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=25559&amp;amp;highlight=form+action&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=25559&amp;amp;highlight=form+action&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not familiar enough with the Spring source to suggest a fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
